  "text": "The LLVM loop vectorization infrastructure is primarily located in the llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/ directory. Here are the five key components:\n\n1. **LoopVectorizePass** (Main Pass Implementation):\n   - **Header**: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h (lines 130-166)\n   - **Implementation**: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp\n   - **Class**: LoopVectorizePass - The primary pass that drives the entire loop vectorization pipeline, managing transformation of vectorizable loops into SIMD code.\n\n2. **LoopVectorizeOptions** (Pass Configuration):\n   - **Location**: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h (lines 85-119)\n   - **Class**: LoopVectorizeOptions - Struct that controls vectorization behavior, including InterleaveOnlyWhenForced and VectorizeOnlyWhenForced flags.\n\n3. **LoopVectorizationLegality** (Legality Checker):\n   - **Header**: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.h\n   - **Implementation**: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.cpp\n   - **Class**: LoopVectorizationLegality (line 261 in header) - Determines whether a loop can be legally vectorized by checking constraints like induction variables, reductions, memory dependencies, and data types.\n\n4. **LoopVectorizationCostModel** (Profitability Analysis):\n   - **Location**: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp (line 882)\n   - **Class**: LoopVectorizationCostModel - Analyzes whether vectorization is profitable by estimating execution costs and determining optimal vectorization factors using TargetTransformInfo.\n\n5. **VPlan** (Vectorization Plan Data Structure):\n   - **Header**: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h (line 4491)\n   - **Implementation**: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp\n   - **Class**: VPlan - Represents a vectorization plan with regions, blocks, and recipes that model how the loop will be vectorized before code generation."
}

